Steps to assign user to admin:

=> Remove a User from the admin Role
php artisan tinker

use App\Models\User;

$user = User::where('email', 'alamba@sansa.org.za')->first();
$user->assignRole('admin');
$user->removeRole('admin');

=> Assign a Different User as Admin
$newAdmin = User::where('email', 'alamba@sansa.org.za')->first();
$newAdmin->assignRole('admin');

=> Remove All Roles From a User
$user = User::where('email', 'mabheka@gmail.com')->first();
$user->syncRoles([]);

=> List All Roles of a User
$user->getRoleNames();

If you have this "Spatie\Permission\Exceptions\RoleDoesNotExist  There is no role named `admin` for guard `web`."
use Spatie\Permission\Models\Role;

// Create the 'admin' role (if it doesn't exist)
Role::firstOrCreate(['name' => 'admin', 'guard_name' => 'web']);

Make sure is_admin = true
UPDATE users SET is_admin = true WHERE email = 'alamba@sansa.org.za';


